[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Investigating dependencies and tests**\n\nI need to use a specific document setup. It looks like parquet-jackson might be a fork or shade of Jackson to avoid conflicts for users of Jackson. This means tests can directly utilize the shaded Jackson API for JSON serialization, without needing external services. I’m wondering if there’s an extra dependency. Existing tests only involve parquet-jackson, assertj, and adding `opens java.util` for private reflection. I need to check if Jackson needs to be updated to 1.16, and if there are optional modules available.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_054ef23724235d28016a3f7db2f06c8190b8721901bfb39e12\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP322BUpTvFuNhvmiWW2KSMNK0nUVGbk5KkAX_GWH2HtByNP-a4eEPccFVR5KTkCXgkcXZgMt8RKZ0ATtva9Xn8L1c5o43ZMQQngCt8LeZR-eVpNH3O-InHpGOvQYrFMjEwBlXVFkLus9jmH7M0MCc7kLpTH_OiePjiUvaD8cCeuQmy_RzkwgITX2cWtgBjisWYY4ilQvFY2icYSTNTO9KOIWL-iUgw8fuBv6SnYT7jH84UHdbkvjBjJYZbTZyUoj1xvvQInzf32QLjbT78LmRZWjMVaWG1jhonilc0RrXOjqZR_n3wgNayyrM6hG93bpznslKPrzuq9UYvUwO3shWYZeSHkhyburpku_CKl6dpPpIe0VAr61LYXKNoney8dRG5zF3wQO6Mqo9_sxgTOmSsiKLIjoYru3wGz41kfYufvktfMJ8OIu1gdC9zp6Q72gzNcrPMPH92MLmNdKNfOkG8Ts4_v43GMin669a0yVsgspiv4uRaz-QSl8LFFMzNEpdoaZ9rHf2MXVX0I0b1Wzip6to57U3qP_6yvUX0vSg-vJqDdTUb3pqfTbYT9rN9_aoBuKwxjjo10lKSTU5MdXGvWN9fnnDqaV9ZEzffYXZywb9PFIsR7Oz1uWZ5ZiW94GVCF0PQ5qE9NjEbnVtUZ1ebUYBnLMGJlzmfcu8ElVxqcXGcrseHE86P3QMpQm_uBxmuPYAwp8uSjA8NtcZfgiOswNB7FHc-CDJZX8Ii2Sk9Npj-Dg254TC69JF7rW6IDyORMhD22bSeyyT_8I_htg6RAI3bpQ2rwovyzyf7RDKVWR7QypjNuAXJUsviEPMUmreMxmre_60IsI-Pd85VFPsqdkeJDPMg4CJRmidcsw_JRPOsb5sQM_iz166kPcf-TotJUQg2z4uR5AgEFJNYEc7ElkUEkdzhxOCQOR5RHchG5ODj_3tLCz5A4txU5AeeTPRM0sxpxB7QCV6JMiX312kjV_WzDXmOQqXwRgieofMPsFgBq2lPek-_WlpFjLEYVNySr8zzgYRvjJdnL50vj0mdus-ryNE8Yt0Tm_e81Cmw-t29E5nrojFPnMpGc__YQIyWd2xCo6aNgNIl5wln6j_qOPeeMv9oUQve7inAvxg_rjvR8FiZBk4ZvWexjB09lGVRXmLp3_fUq-